section.section:
"Portable electronics" includes:
cellular or satellite phones;
pagers;
personal global positioning satellite units;
portable computers;
portable audio listening, video viewing, or recording devices;
digital cameras;
video camcorders;
portable gaming systems;
docking stations; and
automatic answering devices.

"Portable electronics insurance" means insurance that provides coverage for the repair or replacement of portable electronics, including coverage against one or more of the following causes of loss:
loss by disappearance;
theft;
mechanical failure;
malfunction;
damage; and
any other applicable peril, as approved by the Commissioner.
